These shallots come peeled to save prep time.

description: Broccoli florets are small, bite-sized pieces of broccoli that have been removed from the stem and are often used in a variety of recipes, including salads, stir-fries, and soups. They are rich in vitamins and minerals, particularly vitamin C and vitamin K, as well as dietary fiber. Broccoli florets can be eaten raw or cooked and are versatile and easy to incorporate into a wide range of dishes. They have a mild, slightly sweet flavor and a slightly crunchy texture when raw, and become tender and soft when cooked.
name: Split Broccoli Florets

description: Cole slaw is a type of salad made from shredded cabbage and sometimes other vegetables like carrots, onions, or peppers. The vegetables are typically mixed with a dressing, often made from mayonnaise or vinegar, and sometimes with added herbs and spices. Cole slaw is a popular side dish in many cuisines and is often served with grilled or fried foods, such as burgers, hot dogs, or fried chicken. It can also be used as a topping for sandwiches, tacos, or wraps.

description: Celery is a crisp, crunchy vegetable that is widely enjoyed for its refreshing taste and versatility in the kitchen. It is a member of the Apiaceae family, which also includes carrots, parsley, and fennel, and is known for its long, green stalks that are often used in cooking and as a healthy snack. The stalks of celery are firm and fibrous, with a delicate, slightly bitter taste that is often described as "earthy." This is pre-diced to save on labor.

description: Sliced red onions are a versatile and flavorful ingredient that are made by slicing fresh red onions into thin, circular pieces. They have a pungent and slightly sweet taste, and are often used in a wide range of culinary applications. Sliced red onions are a popular ingredient in salads, sandwiches, wraps, and burgers, where their crisp texture and bold flavor add a zesty and refreshing taste. They can also be used as a topping for pizzas, or as an ingredient in dips, spreads, and sauces.

description: Strawberries are a bright red, juicy and sweet fruit that are a popular and delicious addition to a wide range of recipes and desserts. They are typically in season during the summer months, but are available year-round thanks to modern growing and transportation methods. Strawberries are incredibly versatile and can be used in a variety of recipes, from sweet to savory. They are often used in desserts like cakes, pies, and ice cream, and can also be added to salads, smoothies, and other dishes for a sweet and tangy flavor.
name: Strawberries

description: Limes are a type of citrus fruit that is known for its acidic, tangy, and sour taste. They have a thin, green and smooth skin and are typically available all year round. They are smaller and rounder than lemons and have a green, acidic flesh. Limes are a good source of vitamin C, folate and potassium. They are used in a wide range of culinary dishes and drinks, as well as for their juice and zest, which are used as a natural flavoring and preservative. Limes are considered as a staple in many kitchens around the world for their unique taste and versatility, especially in the cuisine of Latin America, the Caribbean, and Southeast Asia.
name: Limes

description: Seedless watermelons have the same trademark two-toned variegated green skin and juicy, sweet red flesh as the seeded version. Though it lacks the large hard black seeds of traditional watermelons, the Seedless watermelon can contain small white seeds that are soft and completely edible.
name: Seedless Watermelons

description: Mixed cherry tomatoes are a variety of small, bite-sized tomatoes that come in various colors such as red, orange, yellow, and sometimes green. They are typically sweeter and less acidic than regular tomatoes and can have a variety of flavors ranging from tangy to sweet. They are often used in salads, as a snack, or as a garnish.
name: Mixed Cherry Tomatoes

description: Large, globular tomatoes have bright red, smooth skin and meaty flesh with a classic tomato favor. Perfect for slicing, chopping, and any other preparation. Slightly smaller than 5x5 tomatoes.

description: Celery is a crisp, crunchy vegetable that is widely enjoyed for its refreshing taste and versatility in the kitchen. It is a member of the Apiaceae family, which also includes carrots, parsley, and fennel, and is known for its long, green stalks that are often used in cooking and as a healthy snack. The stalks of celery are firm and fibrous, with a delicate, slightly bitter taste that is often described as "earthy." The leaves of the celery plant are also edible and have a slightly stronger flavor than the stalks. The innermost part of the stalks is the most tender and is commonly used in recipes that call for finely chopped celery.
name: Celery

description: Russian Banana potatoes are a small, elongated, and waxy variety of potato with a thin, delicate skin. They have a buttery and nutty flavor, making them a popular choice for roasting, baking, and grilling. Russian Banana potatoes have a creamy texture that holds up well when cooked, making them an excellent ingredient for use in potato salads, soups, and stews.
name: Russian Banana Fingerling Potatoes

description: Portabella mushrooms are large, circular mushrooms with a rounded, earthen tan flat cap and nearly black gills. Their thick white stem is edible but often removed. Portabella mushrooms have a characteristically rich and meaty texture and flavor.
name: Portabella Mushrooms

description: Watermelon radish is a type of radish that is large and round, with a green and white outer skin that covers a vibrant pink, juicy flesh that resembles watermelon. The flesh has a crisp and slightly sweet taste, similar to a mild radish flavor with a hint of watermelon. Watermelon radish is often used raw in salads, sandwiches, or as a garnish for various dishes, and is known for its striking appearance and unique flavor.
name: Watermelon Radishes

description: Jumbo asparagus is a type of asparagus with larger and thicker stalks compared to other varieties of asparagus. The spears are typically tender and succulent with a slightly sweet, earthy flavor. Jumbo asparagus is commonly served roasted, grilled, or saut�ed and can be used in a variety of dishes such as salads, pastas, or served as a side dish.

description: Also known as French green beans, Haricots verts are longer and thinner than American green bean varieties and tend to be more tender and have a more robust flavor.
name: Haricot Vert (French Beans)

description: Carrots are bright orange, cylindrical and tapered roots with green tops resembling the lacy look and grassy taste of parsley. Their flesh is snappy and crisp with quintessentially earthy and sweet flavors.

description: Idaho potatoes are often called "chef's potatoes" because they have the perfect amount of starchiness making them ideal for a variety of preparations. Idaho potatoes have fine, brown, sandpaper-textured skin and white flesh that is floury and fluffy when cooked with a smooth, buttery flavor.
name: Idaho Potatoes

description: Yukon Gold potatoes are round to oblong and slightly flattened. Their smooth, golden yellow-brown skin is eye free and is speckled with brown spots, and their inner flesh is moist, yellow and waxy. Yukon Gold potatoes are creamy when cooked with a rich, buttery flavor. A potatoes are larger and more uniform in shape and size.
name: Yukon A Potatoes

description: Jumbo yams, also known as sweet potatoes, are a type of root vegetable that is larger in size compared to regular sweet potatoes. They have a dark, reddish-brown skin and deep orange flesh that is sweet and moist. They can be prepared in various ways, including baking, boiling, roasting, and mashing. They are also a great ingredient for pies, bread, and casseroles. Jumbo yams can be stored in a cool, dry place.
name: Jumbo Sweet Potatoes

description: Oyster mushrooms have gray, fluted caps similar in shape to an oyster, with white gills that extend down to a very short or nonexistent stem. Oyster mushrooms are soft and have a slightly chewy texture and delicate, mild flavor.
name: Oyster Mushrooms

description: Leeks are a type of vegetable that belong to the Allium family, which also includes onions, garlic, and shallots. They have a long, cylindrical shape and a white bulb at the base, with flat green leaves that form a fan-like pattern at the top. Leeks have a sweet, mild flavor that is similar to onions but more delicate, with a slightly herbal and grassy taste. One of the unique characteristics of leeks is that they are a multi-layered vegetable, which means that they have a complex texture and flavor profile. The white part is the most tender and has a mild flavor, while the green part is more fibrous and has a slightly stronger taste.
name: Leeks

description: Jalapeno peppers are conical-shaped pods with smooth, green skin. Inside the semi-thick, green flesh is an inner cavity with a thin white membrane laden with small white seeds that carry a lot of the jalapeno's heat. Jalapenos are crisp and juicy, with a spicy, vegetal flavor.
name: Jalapeno Pepper

The stalks of celery are firm and fibrous, with a delicate, slightly bitter taste that is often described as "earthy." This is pre-diced to save on labor.

description: Red cabbage is rounded and wrapped in tightly wound, waxy purple and burgundy leaves. The flavor of the cabbage is more bold, cruciferous and peppery than green cabbage.
name: Red Cabbage

description: Yukon potatoes are round to oblong and slightly flattened with moist and waxy, yellow flesh. They are creamy when cooked with a rich, buttery flavor. These potatoes come peeled to save prep time.
name: Whole Peeled Yukon Potato

description: Silver Dollar mushrooms are large, white mushrooms with smooth rounded caps and short truncated stems. They range in color from stark white to brown depending on when they are harvested. Silver Dollar mushrooms have a mild meaty flavor that is elevated when cooked.
name: Silver Dollar Mushrooms

description: Created especially for chefs, this is a mix of Yellow Oyster, Shiitake, Lions Mane, Maitake, & White Hon Shimeji mushrooms, all individually packed and ready to use in a variety of applications. What sets this Fresh Mushroom Mix apart is its versatility and umami-rich flavor profile. Whether you're sautéing them to savory perfection, simmering them in sauces, or using them as a flavorful base for your dishes, this mix will infuse your culinary creations with a depth of flavor and a delightful medley of textures. Our Fresh Mushroom Mix is a symphony of mushroom varieties, carefully curated to offer you a diverse selection of flavors, textures, and culinary potential.
name: Mushroom Mix

description: This is a mix of purple, red, and white creamer potatoes. Creamer potatoes are petite, round to oblong potatoes with thin skin and a creamy consistency when cooked.
name: Rainbow Creamer Potatoes

description: Orange bell peppers have a rounded, squat shape and glossy, bright orange skin. Inside the thick, orange flesh is an inner cavity with several edible but bitter white seeds and a spongy white core. Orange peppers are crisp in texture and offer a sweet vegetable flavor with fruity overtones.
name: Imported Orange Peppers

description: Okinawa yams or sweet potatoes have buff beige skin and violet purple flesh, usually with white striations. Unlike most sweet potatoes, Okinawa's have a very starchy texture. When cooked, their flavor is earthy and incredibly sweet.
name: Purple Okinawa (Sweet Potatoes) Yams

description: White asparagus spears are pearly white, thick and rounded. Their flavor is mild and slightly herbaceous with nutty, earthy notes of artichoke and fresh white corn.
name: White Asparagus

description: Brussels sprouts are a nutritious and delicious vegetable that are commonly halved for cooking. This process exposes the inner layers of the sprouts, allowing for even cooking and caramelization. These halved Brussels sprouts are perfect for roasting, saut�ing, or grilling. They have a slightly sweet and nutty flavor.
name: Brussel Sprouts Halved

description: Fresh horseradish is a root vegetable that is known for its pungent, spicy flavor and distinct aroma. Fresh horseradish is typically beige or brown on the outside and white on the inside, with a gnarled and irregular shape. It is usually grated or finely chopped and used as a condiment, seasoning, or ingredient in many culinary dishes. When grated, fresh horseradish releases a potent and sinus-clearing aroma that is often used in traditional dishes such as roast beef, prime rib, and seafood dishes. It can also be used as a flavoring for sauces, dressings, and dips.
name: Horseradish Root

description: Orange habanero is a type of hot pepper that is small and lantern-shaped with a bright orange color. It is known for its fruity and citrusy flavor with a spicy kick that can range from mild to very hot. Orange habanero peppers are often used in salsas, hot sauces, marinades, and spice blends to add heat and flavor to dishes.
name: Orange Habenaro Peppers

description: King Oyster mushrooms, also known as "King Trumpet" mushrooms, are a type of edible mushroom that is highly prized for its meaty texture and delicious flavor. These mushrooms are native to the Mediterranean region, but are now grown and consumed in many parts of the world. King Oyster mushrooms have a cylindrical shape with a pale white color and a thick stem. They have a firm and meaty texture that is often compared to that of scallops or abalone. These mushrooms are often used in savory dishes, such as soups, stews, and stir-fries, and can also be roasted or grilled to bring out their flavor.
name: King Trumpet Mushrooms

description: Our Diced Celery is a celebration of freshness. Each celery stalk is meticulously diced to perfection saving you valuable prep time, preserving the vibrant green color and the crisp, juicy texture that embodies their natural goodness. What sets these diced celery pieces apart is their versatility and subtle flavor. Whether you're adding them to soups and stocks for depth, using them as a crunchy garnish, or incorporating them into creative recipes, these diced celery pieces will infuse your dishes with a burst of freshness and a hint of earthy goodness. With our diced celery, you can enjoy the convenience of a high-quality product that's ready to enhance your dishes, allowing you to focus on perfecting your culinary vision.

description: Sugar cane skewers are an eco-friendly alternative to traditional wooden or metal skewers. These skewers are made from the stalk of sugar cane plants and are a great choice for grilling meats, vegetables, and fruits. They are durable and heat-resistant, and won't leave any taste or odor on your food. Sugar cane skewers are also biodegradable and compostable, making them an environmentally responsible choice for outdoor barbecues, parties, and other events.
name: Sugar Cane Skewers
